No.

618
00:25:35,935 --> 00:25:38,380
Well, her breathing
has stabilized for now.

619
00:25:38,404 --> 00:25:40,114
How long have you been together?

620
00:25:40,138 --> 00:25:42,256
Twenty-seven years.

621
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:46,043
Kerry?

622
00:25:49,731 --> 00:25:51,343
Could you excuse
us for a moment?

623
00:25:51,367 --> 00:25:52,367
Sure.

624
00:25:59,007 --> 00:26:01,853
What are you doing?

625
00:26:01,877 --> 00:26:04,940
She talked to her
brother twice in 10 years.

626
00:26:04,964 --> 00:26:07,559
Yes, and she didn't grant
her partner power of attorney.

627
00:26:07,583 --> 00:26:09,861
I'm trying to find a legal
way to fulfill her wishes.

628
00:26:09,885 --> 00:26:12,364
Twenty-seven years. That
should count for something.

629
00:26:12,388 --> 00:26:14,632
The woman has a
reasonable chance of survival.

630
00:26:14,656 --> 00:26:16,235
But what kind of life?

631
00:26:16,259 --> 00:26:18,370
Intubation is an
appropriate step

632
00:26:18,394 --> 00:26:20,038
unless she has an
advanced directive.

633
00:26:20,062 --> 00:26:22,658
The only person who can
change that is the next of kin.

634
00:26:22,682 --> 00:26:24,743
She is the next of kin.

635
00:26:24,767 --> 00:26:26,311
They lived their lives together.

636
00:26:26,335 --> 00:26:27,812
We should treat
them like a couple.

637
00:26:27,836 --> 00:26:30,638
I agree. The law doesn't.

638
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:33,168
If her sats drop below 80

639
00:26:33,192 --> 00:26:35,075
before her brother
calls back, tube her.

640
00:26:35,995 --> 00:26:37,172
No.

641
00:26:37,196 --> 00:26:39,073
What?

642
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:40,459
If you want to
manage it this way,

643
00:26:40,483 --> 00:26:43,333
then you should manage it.

644
00:26:44,753 --> 00:26:46,130
Okay. Fine.

645
00:26:46,154 --> 00:26:47,454
Give me the chart.

646
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:04,387
Thank you. I just...
I need a picture.

647
00:27:05,007 --> 00:27:06,551
I understand.

648
00:27:06,575 --> 00:27:08,670
Should we use the
name? You don't want to?

649
00:27:08,694 --> 00:27:11,456
No, I think we should.

650
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,925
There's only one boy's
name that we could agree on.

651
00:27:13,949 --> 00:27:15,127
What's that?

652
00:27:15,151 --> 00:27:16,761
Julian.

653
00:27:16,785 --> 00:27:18,397
It's a nice name.

654
00:27:18,421 --> 00:27:20,021
Yeah.

655
00:27:23,025 --> 00:27:25,570
How much longer?

656
00:27:25,594 --> 00:27:26,610
I don't know.

657
00:27:27,546 --> 00:27:28,690
It could be a few minutes.

658
00:27:28,714 --> 00:27:31,481
It could be a few hours.

659
00:27:37,656 --> 00:27:38,822
Let's take him outside.

660
00:27:39,425 --> 00:27:41,235
What?

661
00:27:41,259 --> 00:27:44,456
We'll take him to
a lake or a park.

662
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:46,997
If he's gonna die, I don't
want him to die in here.

663
00:27:49,201 --> 00:27:51,262
We have to wait for the priest.

664
00:27:51,286 --> 00:27:52,664
Is he coming?

665
00:27:52,688 --> 00:27:54,388
I'll check again.

666
00:27:56,208 --> 00:27:57,208
Abby.

667
00:28:03,164 --> 00:28:05,165
Excuse me. I'll be right back.

668
00:28:08,003 --> 00:28:09,898
I paged you three times.

669
00:28:09,922 --> 00:28:11,900
We had a 22-week birth
here. The baby's alive.

670
00:28:11,924 --> 00:28:14,152
You had a patient
upstairs who needed you.

671
00:28:14,176 --> 00:28:15,153
Did she deliver?

672
00:28:15,177 --> 00:28:17,105
Yes, she delivered.

673
00:28:17,129 --> 00:28:19,240
Shoulder dystocia.

674
00:28:19,264 --> 00:28:20,575
Is the baby okay?

675
00:28:20,599 --> 00:28:23,484
Well, apart from a broken
clavicle, he'll be fine.

676
00:28:24,937 --> 00:28:27,332
She was really scared,
and she was asking for you.

677
00:28:27,356 --> 00:28:29,501
Look, if you wanna take
shifts as an OB nurse,

678
00:28:29,525 --> 00:28:31,787
I need you to work
as an OB nurse.

679
00:28:31,811 --> 00:28:33,889
You cannot let these women
grow dependent on you,

680
00:28:33,913 --> 00:28:36,357
and then just walk out on
them when you got an excuse.

681
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:37,758
I was not looking for an excuse,

682
00:28:37,782 --> 00:28:39,961
I was taking care of
this woman and her baby.

683
00:28:39,985 --> 00:28:42,063
There are other people
down here who can do that.

684
00:28:42,087 --> 00:28:43,698
Your job is upstairs.

685
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:46,000
Janet, I'm sorry.
It was my call.

686
00:28:46,024 --> 00:28:47,269
I asked Abby to stay.

687
00:28:47,293 --> 00:28:49,137
These parents are
completely distraught.

688
00:28:49,161 --> 00:28:50,689
There's nothing we can do,

689
00:28:50,713 --> 00:28:52,157
but they need support,

690
00:28:52,181 --> 00:28:54,981
and Abby's been with
them since the birth.

691
00:28:57,219 --> 00:28:59,719
Just don't ignore
my page. I'm sorry.

692
00:29:01,957 --> 00:29:03,268
Thank you.

693
00:29:03,292 --> 00:29:06,037
No. You're doing the hard part.

694
00:29:06,061 --> 00:29:07,038
Is he still breathing?

695
00:29:07,062 --> 00:29:08,456
Agonally.

696
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:10,125
Let me know when
you need to pronounce.

697
00:29:10,149 --> 00:29:11,793
Okay.

698
00:29:11,817 --> 00:29:14,496
Last time I got heated
blankets and an extra pillow.

699
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:15,997
Phew.

700
00:29:16,021 --> 00:29:17,231
What's open, Shirley?

701
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:18,600
Depends on what you have.

702
00:29:18,624 --> 00:29:21,102
Revision of an AV
graft, left forearm.

703
00:29:21,126 --> 00:29:22,971
Patient named Fletcher?
How did you know?

704
00:29:22,995 --> 00:29:26,174
Dr. Romano warned me
you'd try to bring him up.

705
00:29:26,198 --> 00:29:28,543
Yeah, well, it's my call.
Just, uh, give me a room.

706
00:29:28,567 --> 00:29:29,928
