708
00:29:32,288 --> 00:29:34,838
He actually said he'd fire me.

709
00:29:38,844 --> 00:29:42,590
Okay. Okay, well, please hurry.

710
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:44,280
Thank you.

711
00:29:46,117 --> 00:29:47,228
That was the priest.

712
00:29:47,252 --> 00:29:49,364
He finally talked that
woman down from a ledge.

713
00:29:49,388 --> 00:29:51,366
He's gonna get over
here and baptize this baby.

714
00:29:51,390 --> 00:29:52,617
How long has it been?

715
00:29:52,641 --> 00:29:54,586
Almost five hours. Wow.

716
00:29:54,610 --> 00:29:56,988
He's really hanging on.

717
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:59,107
Maybe the mother's right.

718
00:29:59,131 --> 00:30:00,242
Maybe he is a miracle.

719
00:30:00,266 --> 00:30:05,463
In 10, 15 years, we
might be able to help.

720
00:30:05,487 --> 00:30:06,664
You know, they wanted to try.

721
00:30:06,688 --> 00:30:08,800
We could intubate
him, just in case.

722
00:30:08,824 --> 00:30:10,784
Abby... I know.

723
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:13,722
It's his time on Earth,

724
00:30:13,746 --> 00:30:16,813
and all you can do is
make it a good time.

725
00:30:19,935 --> 00:30:21,135
I think he stopped breathing.

726
00:30:22,788 --> 00:30:24,087
Here we go.

727
00:30:27,809 --> 00:30:29,654
That's not a respirator?

728
00:30:29,678 --> 00:30:32,490
No. It provides positive
pressure to her lungs

729
00:30:32,514 --> 00:30:34,765
so she doesn't have to
work so hard to breathe.

730
00:30:37,936 --> 00:30:40,176
Her father died of lung cancer.

731
00:30:43,208 --> 00:30:44,652
I remember Glenda
and her brother

732
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:47,672
fighting outside the ICU.

733
00:30:47,696 --> 00:30:49,174
Danny couldn't let go,

734
00:30:49,198 --> 00:30:51,942
and Glenda couldn't watch
her father suffer like that.

735
00:30:51,966 --> 00:30:53,933
You know, all those tubes.

736
00:30:56,304 --> 00:30:58,415
After her first stroke,
Glenda made me promise

737
00:30:58,439 --> 00:31:00,959
to never let her die like that.

738
00:31:02,210 --> 00:31:04,628
We'll do everything we
can to reach her brother.

739
00:31:05,714 --> 00:31:08,114
He doesn't know her like I do.

740
00:31:12,771 --> 00:31:14,938
I love her.

741
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:22,095
I don't wanna lose her,
but I know what she wants.

742
00:31:27,336 --> 00:31:29,214
His breathing just
slowed down for a second,

743
00:31:29,238 --> 00:31:31,366
and then it just... It stopped.

744
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:33,790
Please, if you
could do anything.

745
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:37,841
Is there a heartbeat?

746
00:31:39,048 --> 00:31:40,048
No.

747
00:31:46,888 --> 00:31:47,983
You wanna call it?

748
00:31:48,007 --> 00:31:49,305
Oh, God.

749
00:31:53,462 --> 00:31:54,456
Abby?

750
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:56,157
Yeah.

751
00:31:56,181 --> 00:31:57,364
